\f1\fs28 \cf0 Only the Upper Case letters and the numerals are used for registration plates. The capital I, which is the same as the 1, is not used. The Q is generally unused but may still be required for updating old plates.\
\
--------------------------------------------------\
\
For designers, the font is completed with small capitals for the lower case, currency symbols, punctuation marks, printers' symbols and accented characters.\
\
Version 5 contains heavier small caps characters. These better match the weight of the uppercase letters and make the font more useful for mixed case text.\
\
Version 5 also includes numerous outline and spacing improvements.}